snippet.textDisplay:
Naaah, hate that form factor. And it still looks like a mini PC/mini-fridge. And yeah, it looks lazy. Would be a pain in the ass to fit in my tv case. Prefer the flat VCR designs. Flat design wasn’t broke, why fix it, except laziness? Hope PS5 doesn’t go this route.

Not sure about that proprietary memory card either. Better be sold zero profit for Xbox and not overpriced like Vita memory. But nonetheless extra cost to make the slot for that card which perhaps could’ve just been used just to buy a bigger SSD in the first place. Maybe it’s a good thing, maybe not. Wait for price before deciding. Skeptical, especially will it really work as well as the built in memory or will it work slower? Or perhaps built in memory was slowed down to match the speed of the memory cart? Wouldn’t trust Microsoft not to do shady things like that.

And wtf, still no built in battery for the controller???? Come on.

If they have good games, I’ll buy, but won’t like that console form factor. Just won’t look right in my entertainment table. Hope PS doesn’t go this route.
